<h2>Color</h2>

<p>Colorize text with color utilities.</p>

{% snippet %}
<p class="text-primary">.text-primary</p>
<p class="text-red">.text-red</p>
<p class="text-pink">.text-pink</p>
<p class="text-purple">.text-purple</p>
<p class="text-blue">.text-blue</p>
<p class="text-green">.text-green</p>
<p class="text-yellow">.text-yellow</p>
<p class="text-orange">.text-orange</p>
<p class="text-white bg-black">.text-white</p>
<p class="text-gray">.text-gray</p>
<p class="text-gray-dark">.text-gray-dark</p>
<p class="text-black">.text-black</p>
{% endsnippet %}

<h2>Background color</h2>

<p>Similar to the contextual text color classes, easily set the background of an element to any contextual class. Background utilities don't set any color, so you may use <code>.text-*</code> utilities in conjunciton.</p>

{% snippet %}
<p class="p-m p-m bg-primary text-white">.bg-primary</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-red text-white">.bg-red</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-pink text-white">.bg-pink</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-purple text-white">.bg-purple</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-blue text-white">.bg-blue</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-green">.bg-green</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-yellow">.bg-yellow</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-orange">.bg-orange</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-white">.bg-white</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-gray">.bg-gray</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-gray-dark text-white">.bg-gray-dark</p>
<p class="p-m p-m bg-black text-white">.bg-black</p>
{% endsnippet %}

